WEBVTT

00:02.000 --> 00:07.000
Downloaded from
YTS.MX

00:08.000 --> 00:13.000
Official YIFY movies site:
YTS.MX

00:46.208 --> 00:47.625
<i>Look at the stars.</i>

00:47.791 --> 00:49.791
<i>Whenever you feel alone,</i>

00:49.958 --> 00:52.083
<i>the great kings of the past</i>

00:52.250 --> 00:54.958
<i>will always be up there
to guide you.</i>

00:55.791 --> 00:57.125
<i>And so will I.</i>

02:15.416 --> 02:19.541
My friends, the time of
my family's growth is upon us.

02:20.625 --> 02:22.999
This home we share
is the fulfillment

02:23.000 --> 02:24.500
of my father's vision.

02:24.666 --> 02:26.749
How wonderful is it
that Nala and I

02:26.750 --> 02:28.666
get to continue his dream

02:28.833 --> 02:31.415
and make even greater
the Circle of Life?

02:38.458 --> 02:40.875
Nala, my love, I'm on my way.

03:18.791 --> 03:20.458
Simba...

03:21.208 --> 03:22.583
I'm here.

03:23.958 --> 03:25.250
I'm here.

03:38.375 --> 03:40.791
Security detail
has arrived!

03:40.958 --> 03:43.458
One gentle reminder:
we are not food.

03:43.625 --> 03:45.625
No, no, no, no, no.
We are just two guys

03:45.791 --> 03:48.083
walking to work through
a pride of hungry lions.

03:48.250 --> 03:50.958
Which is perfectly
normal. I'm not terrified.

03:51.458 --> 03:53.790
Security detail
reporting for duty,

03:53.791 --> 03:55.500
Your Grace, Your Highness...

03:55.666 --> 03:58.083
Ruler of all
four-legged creatures.

03:58.250 --> 04:00.458
And that one
three-legged zebra.

04:00.625 --> 04:02.875
Oh, right, Ron.
That was tragic.

04:03.041 --> 04:04.333
- It was an eat-and-Ron.
- Yeah.

04:04.500 --> 04:06.415
Ron has three legs.
That's still one more than me.

04:06.416 --> 04:07.624
- Well, are those arms or legs?
-  Guys.

04:07.625 --> 04:08.707
I don't know.
I think they're paws.

04:08.708 --> 04:09.790
Guys.

04:09.791 --> 04:12.416
- I consider all those legs.
- Guys! This is serious.

04:12.583 --> 04:14.500
I need you to stay with Kiara
until I get back.

04:14.666 --> 04:17.415
Are you saying
that your security detail

04:17.416 --> 04:20.291
has been called on
to do babysitting?

04:20.458 --> 04:21.874
Pumbaa, we should
really discuss this

04:21.875 --> 04:23.375
because I don't really love...

04:23.541 --> 04:26.000
Guys, I promised her
everything would be okay.

04:26.166 --> 04:27.291
Well, that's one way
to parent.

04:27.458 --> 04:28.500
She's gonna
have to grow up sometime.

04:28.666 --> 04:29.665
What else did you tell her,

04:29.666 --> 04:31.250
that she could be
whatever she wants to be?

04:31.416 --> 04:32.458
That life is fair?

04:32.625 --> 04:34.916
I need you two to try
and act like adults, okay?

04:35.083 --> 04:38.125
Don't scare Kiara.
And most of all, no stories.

04:38.291 --> 04:39.749
- No stories?
- Wait a second.

04:39.750 --> 04:40.832
I know where your head goes.

04:40.833 --> 04:42.458
I grew up with you two.
Promise me.

04:42.625 --> 04:43.999
Okay. You know what,
you know what, you know what?

04:44.000 --> 04:45.416
Fine. No stories.

04:45.583 --> 04:46.958
Speak for yourself, Pumbaa.

04:47.125 --> 04:49.165
No. Pssh.
We'll tell a story anyway.

04:49.166 --> 04:50.415
Okay, we'll tell
him that we're not gonna

04:50.416 --> 04:51.499
tell a story and then
we're gonna tell a story.

04:51.500 --> 04:52.791
- He can't stop us.
- Are you guys serious?

04:52.958 --> 04:54.500
I'm clearly within earshot.

04:54.666 --> 04:55.791
Dad.

04:58.708 --> 05:00.333
Hey, little one.

05:01.791 --> 05:04.166
Dad, the storm's coming,
and I'm scared.

05:04.333 --> 05:05.833
I wanna go with you and Mom.

05:06.166 --> 05:07.541
- Don't be scared, my love.
- Mmm.

05:07.750 --> 05:09.750
Timon and Pumbaa
will watch you while I'm gone.

05:09.916 --> 05:11.375
Be brave now, Kiara.

05:12.208 --> 05:14.000
Be brave.

05:18.458 --> 05:21.082
Okay!
We've prepared a story.

05:23.333 --> 05:24.625
<i>Scar looked at us.</i>

05:24.791 --> 05:26.875
<i>He knew it was
the end of the line.</i>

05:27.041 --> 05:28.875
<i>I could smell the fear.</i>

05:29.041 --> 05:31.166
<i>That was actually me,
but yes.</i>

05:48.833 --> 05:50.791
<i>So you two
defeated Scar?</i>

05:50.958 --> 05:52.041
And then you ate him?

05:52.208 --> 05:54.208
Honestly, one of the best
meals I ever had.

05:54.375 --> 05:56.291
My dad told me
he defeated Scar.

05:56.458 --> 05:57.832
Well, okay. But your dad,

05:57.833 --> 05:59.416
as we all know,
is a pathological liar.

05:59.583 --> 06:01.666
He's always lyin'. Get it?

06:05.291 --> 06:07.333
I'm scared.
I want Mom and Dad.

06:07.500 --> 06:08.625
Look, look, look
look, look.

06:08.791 --> 06:10.416
Don't be scared, Kiara.

06:10.583 --> 06:14.000
How about we sing you a song?
And, a-one...

06:14.166 --> 06:16.666
Pumbaa, no, it is
way too early for the song.

06:16.833 --> 06:17.832
It worked on Simba.

06:17.833 --> 06:19.291
He thought he had
murdered his own father.

06:19.458 --> 06:21.291
He was singin' and dancin'
around in seconds.

06:21.458 --> 06:22.874
I can't just
turn it on like that.

06:22.875 --> 06:24.416
I have to be in the moment.

06:24.583 --> 06:25.791
He sang that song
for six years straight.

06:25.958 --> 06:27.375
Well, who didn't?

06:27.541 --> 06:28.665
Look!

06:28.666 --> 06:29.874
- No!
- It's Ron,

06:29.875 --> 06:31.957
the three-legged zebra.
Run for your lives!

06:31.958 --> 06:33.333
He heard what we've been
sayin' about him.

06:33.500 --> 06:36.291
We're sorry, Ron. They were
jokes. They were just jokes!

06:36.666 --> 06:37.916
It's Rafiki.

06:38.083 --> 06:39.915
Rafiki! Rafiki!

06:42.250 --> 06:44.833
Little one,
there's no reason to cry.

06:45.000 --> 06:46.000
My parents...

06:46.541 --> 06:47.540
they're gone.

06:47.541 --> 06:50.208
Hey. Look out there, <i>mdogo.</i>

06:50.708 --> 06:53.250
You see those baobab trees
blowing in the wind?

06:53.750 --> 06:58.041
The roots of those trees are
very strong, like your family.

06:58.208 --> 07:00.083
And, just as they did for you,

07:00.250 --> 07:03.750
your parents have gone to the
ceremonial birthing grounds.

07:03.916 --> 07:06.915
And when they return,
the Circle of Life

07:06.916 --> 07:10.041
will bring a blessing
to you, Kiara,

07:10.208 --> 07:12.540
that you will never forget.

07:12.541 --> 07:13.624
Man, he's good.

07:13.625 --> 07:15.458
He's such
a visual storyteller.

07:15.625 --> 07:17.708
Yet it makes sense
that he lives alone.

07:18.750 --> 07:20.749
I just want the storm to pass,

07:20.750 --> 07:22.999
and then I promise
to be brave.

07:23.000 --> 07:25.708
I'll tell you a secret.

07:25.875 --> 07:28.250
When your father Simba
was your age,

07:28.416 --> 07:30.249
he was afraid of the thunder

07:30.250 --> 07:32.250
and would hide
behind the king.

07:32.416 --> 07:33.625
When did he stop hiding?

07:33.791 --> 07:35.875
One day, during a big storm,

07:36.041 --> 07:38.790
your grandfather Mufasa
took your father

07:38.791 --> 07:41.166
to the very top of Pride Rock,

07:41.333 --> 07:42.833
told him to stand with him

07:43.000 --> 07:44.875
and howl into the wind.

07:45.041 --> 07:47.833
And Simba slowly stepped out
with the king.

07:48.000 --> 07:51.333
And together,
they roared into the night.

07:53.333 --> 07:55.166
But I'm not brave like my dad.

07:55.708 --> 07:57.665
And I could never be
like Mufasa.

07:57.666 --> 08:00.458
Is that so?

08:01.375 --> 08:04.166
Then maybe it's time
I tell you a story.

08:04.750 --> 08:07.458
A story of a cub,
not much bigger than you.

08:07.750 --> 08:11.125
A lion born without a drop
of nobility in his blood.

08:11.583 --> 08:15.125
A lion who would change
our lives forever.

08:15.666 --> 08:17.833
A story! So glad
I brought some crickets.

08:18.000 --> 08:19.708
But go easy. We're in a cave.

08:20.250 --> 08:22.500
This story
begins far beyond

08:22.666 --> 08:24.500
the mountains and the shadows.

08:24.666 --> 08:26.458
On the other side
of the light.

08:26.625 --> 08:30.875
In this place, everything
was dying of thirst

08:31.041 --> 08:33.289
as 20 full moons
had passed without

08:33.291 --> 08:35.541
a single drop of water.

08:35.750 --> 08:38.457
But when the skies
finally opened,

08:39.207 --> 08:41.875
destiny would reign.

09:10.625 --> 09:11.625
Mufasa.

09:12.666 --> 09:15.208
Mufasa! Come see.

09:21.041 --> 09:23.833
Mom, what is that light
way out there?

09:24.000 --> 09:26.666
Oh, that's very special.

09:26.833 --> 09:28.458
Beyond the horizon,

09:28.625 --> 09:31.750
beyond the last cloud
in the sky,

09:31.916 --> 09:34.708
that's a place we call <i>Milele.</i>

09:34.875 --> 09:35.916
<i>Milele?</i>

09:36.083 --> 09:38.375
Hmm. It means, "forever."

09:39.291 --> 09:41.625
Imagine
a kingdom full of life,

09:42.458 --> 09:44.416
water and food,

09:44.583 --> 09:48.375
grass and sky
as far as the eye can see.

09:48.541 --> 09:49.666
Will we ever go there?

09:49.833 --> 09:51.291
Oh, yes, Mufasa.

09:51.500 --> 09:53.458
That's exactly
where we're headed.

09:53.833 --> 09:56.625
But we can also
be there right now.

09:57.041 --> 09:58.708
We can close our eyes.

09:58.875 --> 10:01.166
Let our dreams take us.

