Mufasa, you and Taka together.
That...

37:17.916 --> 37:19.000
- That is home.
- Eshe...

37:19.166 --> 37:20.833
Mufasa, look out there.

37:21.458 --> 37:22.583
Beyond the light...

37:22.750 --> 37:24.041
You know what I see?

37:24.208 --> 37:26.582
I see the place your mother
told you about,

37:26.583 --> 37:28.833
a place beyond
the river's end.

37:29.000 --> 37:30.749
Across the deepest canyon

37:30.750 --> 37:32.291
on the other side
of the mountains,

37:32.458 --> 37:34.875
a place beyond
the horizon itself.

37:35.625 --> 37:37.208
A pride land so green,

37:37.750 --> 37:40.208
so perfect

37:40.708 --> 37:43.416
that to see it is to see

37:43.583 --> 37:44.750
<i>Milele.</i>

37:44.916 --> 37:47.500
Yes. Forever.

37:47.666 --> 37:49.540
My parents spoke
of <i>Milele</i> often.

37:49.541 --> 37:51.750
My mother told me
it was where we were going.

37:51.916 --> 37:53.416
And don't you see, Mufasa?

37:53.583 --> 37:54.708
You must keep going.

37:54.875 --> 37:57.125
You must continue your journey
toward the light.

37:57.291 --> 38:00.125
Please, Eshe.
I can't lose you.

38:00.291 --> 38:02.916
You have my love
always, Mufasa.

38:03.083 --> 38:05.958
But your family is still out
there, waiting for you.

38:06.125 --> 38:07.666
I can feel their presence.

38:07.833 --> 38:09.500
And I know you can, too.

38:10.500 --> 38:11.500
Go.

38:12.125 --> 38:15.250
Go, Mufasa.
Find your way home.

38:23.000 --> 38:26.750
Mother, please forgive me.
I beg you.

38:26.916 --> 38:29.125
There's no need, my love.

38:29.291 --> 38:32.166
Taka, your moment of courage
will come.

38:40.750 --> 38:42.250
Now both of you go.

38:43.250 --> 38:45.250
Go and find your place

38:45.666 --> 38:47.250
in the Circle of Life.

39:05.083 --> 39:08.000
They left their family
never to see them again?

39:08.166 --> 39:09.333
This story is killing me.

39:09.500 --> 39:11.041
It's toying with my emotions.

39:11.208 --> 39:12.666
And here
is the worst part.

39:13.083 --> 39:14.541
- What's that?
- I'm out of crickets.

39:14.708 --> 39:15.958
Oh, maybe that's for the best.

39:16.125 --> 39:17.666
I need a bathroom break
before the second act.

39:17.833 --> 39:19.291
Everyone wait for me.

39:24.541 --> 39:25.541
I am back.

39:25.708 --> 39:26.915
Pumbaa, did you wash
your hooves?

39:26.916 --> 39:27.999
Mm-hmm.

39:28.000 --> 39:29.250
- Pumbaa?
- I did. I did.

39:29.416 --> 39:30.666
-  Pumbaa?
- I'm just gonna walk

39:30.833 --> 39:32.416
- on them again right after.
- Pumbaa?

39:34.583 --> 39:37.000
Rafiki,
did the Outsiders come?

39:37.166 --> 39:38.166
Yes.

39:38.333 --> 39:41.083
And as the hunters led Kiros
into the Valley of Kings,

39:41.333 --> 39:44.625
<i>Obasi and Eshe
stood their ground.</i>

39:57.250 --> 40:00.416
Which one of you is king?

40:00.583 --> 40:03.541
You have no reason
to challenge me.

40:03.708 --> 40:08.208
Does this look
like a challenge, King?

40:08.458 --> 40:11.041
There are rules among lions.

40:11.208 --> 40:12.375
Not anymore.

40:13.208 --> 40:16.041
While you ruled this pride,
I've built my army.

40:16.708 --> 40:18.041
Yours is the last pride

40:18.208 --> 40:21.166
in the Valley of Kings,
which means

40:21.333 --> 40:25.208
everything the light touches
belongs to me.

40:25.375 --> 40:27.041
There will be one ruler.

40:27.208 --> 40:29.833
One Lion King.

40:35.750 --> 40:37.790
<i>♪ You say you're the king ♪</i>

40:37.791 --> 40:41.041
<i>♪ But you lie around
in the shade ♪</i>

40:41.208 --> 40:43.666
<i>♪ Out of shape, unafraid ♪</i>

40:44.791 --> 40:48.041
<i>♪ The moon cuts a path
through the sky ♪</i>

40:48.208 --> 40:50.291
<i>♪ By night or by day ♪</i>

40:50.500 --> 40:52.666
<i>♪ It doesn't obey ♪</i>

40:52.833 --> 40:55.041
<i>♪ And neither do I ♪</i>

40:55.208 --> 40:57.707
<i>♪ You took my son ♪</i>

40:59.541 --> 41:02.291
<i>♪ I hope you can run ♪</i>

41:02.833 --> 41:06.541
<i>♪ 'Cause I'm going to be
the last thing you see ♪</i>

41:06.708 --> 41:08.625
<i>♪ Before you go bye-bye ♪</i>

41:09.125 --> 41:11.041
<i>♪ There you go, bye-bye ♪</i>

41:12.250 --> 41:15.666
<i>♪ Climb every tree
Cross land and sea ♪</i>

41:15.833 --> 41:17.541
<i>♪ I'll make you go bye-bye ♪</i>

41:17.958 --> 41:19.875
<i>♪ I'll make you go bye-bye ♪</i>

41:20.916 --> 41:23.249
<i>♪ Everything
in my clutches, ha! ♪</i>

41:23.250 --> 41:24.666
<i>♪ Bye-bye ♪</i>

41:25.583 --> 41:28.041
<i>♪ Everything
the light touches ♪</i>

41:29.958 --> 41:32.958
<i>♪ The Circle of Life
is a lie ♪</i>

41:33.125 --> 41:34.875
<i>♪ A pretty way to say ♪</i>

41:35.041 --> 41:37.666
<i>♪ There are predators
and prey ♪</i>

41:38.625 --> 41:41.875
<i>♪ That circle of vultures
up high ♪</i>

41:42.041 --> 41:44.208
<i>♪ They keep stealing glances ♪</i>

41:44.375 --> 41:46.416
<i>♪ They don't like
your chances ♪</i>

41:46.583 --> 41:48.875
<i>♪ And neither do I ♪</i>

41:49.208 --> 41:52.250
<i>♪ I run my pride ♪</i>

41:53.583 --> 41:56.000
<i>♪ You run and hide ♪</i>

41:57.000 --> 42:00.500
<i>♪ 'Cause I'm going to be
the last thing you see ♪</i>

42:00.666 --> 42:02.500
<i>♪ Before you go bye-bye ♪</i>

42:02.916 --> 42:04.791
<i>♪ There you go, bye-bye ♪</i>

42:05.791 --> 42:09.500
<i>♪ Climb every tree
Cross land and sea ♪</i>

42:09.666 --> 42:11.708
<i>♪ Until you go bye-bye ♪</i>

42:11.875 --> 42:13.708
<i>♪ Will you go bye-bye? ♪</i>

42:14.750 --> 42:18.166
<i>♪ Bye-bye,
for vengeance is mine ♪</i>

42:19.083 --> 42:22.000
<i>♪ If I'm the last of my line ♪</i>

42:22.166 --> 42:27.958
<i>♪ I must be strong ♪</i>

42:28.125 --> 42:29.333
<i>♪ Gotta go bye-bye ♪</i>

42:29.791 --> 42:31.625
<i>♪ I'll make you go bye-bye ♪</i>

42:36.958 --> 42:38.166
<i>♪ Bye-bye ♪</i>

42:46.000 --> 42:48.541
We have to move.
They'll be tracking us.

42:49.083 --> 42:50.583
- Taka!
-  What if you're wrong?

42:51.000 --> 42:52.000
What if they're okay?

42:52.125 --> 42:54.416
They live in you now.

42:54.833 --> 42:56.416
Follow me, brother.

42:57.208 --> 42:58.458
We have to move...

42:59.375 --> 43:00.583
together.

43:25.291 --> 43:26.791
Run, Mufasa.

43:27.708 --> 43:29.500
Run!

43:30.750 --> 43:31.750
Hunters.

43:31.916 --> 43:33.916
-  What's the plan?
-  Uh...

43:34.291 --> 43:36.541
Run! Very fast!

43:42.083 --> 43:43.541
This way!

43:58.166 --> 43:59.416
Back to the trees.

43:59.583 --> 44:01.250
We're trapped.
We have to swim.

44:01.416 --> 44:02.833
No, we have to fight.

44:03.000 --> 44:04.458
If we fight, we die.

44:04.625 --> 44:06.000
But if we swim, we drown.

44:06.166 --> 44:08.250
Okay, I didn't
want to do this,

44:08.416 --> 44:10.500
- but I command you to swim!
- You what?

44:10.666 --> 44:13.291
You pledged your loyalty.
I command you to swim.

44:13.458 --> 44:15.958
Taka, this is not the time
for jokes.

44:30.541 --> 44:33.083
Which one of you
killed my son?

44:33.250 --> 44:34.832
I did.
This lion with me is nothing

44:34.833 --> 44:36.415
but a stray. Let him go.

44:36.416 --> 44:38.208
Kiros, the other is no stray.

44:38.375 --> 44:40.125
He holds the blood
of the pride.

44:41.666 --> 44:44.208
The last blood
of the king? Hmm.

44:45.458 --> 44:48.207
Blood for blood.

45:04.666 --> 45:05.958
They're coming!

45:06.583 --> 45:07.708
What do we do?

45:07.875 --> 45:09.166
We find the advantage?

45:09.333 --> 45:10.374
What advantage?

45:10.375 --> 45:12.916
We're on a rock
in the middle of the water!

45:13.750 --> 45:16.416
Taka, this is it.
We go for the king.

45:25.916 --> 45:27.083
Mufasa, I'm ready.

45:27.875 --> 45:29.416
Just one last thing.

45:29.583 --> 45:30.625
- What?
- Chin up!

45:31.625 --> 45:33.333
Taka!

45:33.583 --> 45:36.249
This was a bad idea.

45:45.041 --> 45:46.374
Mufasa!

45:46.375 --> 45:47.624
Mufasa!

45:55.208 --> 45:56.415
-  Mufasa...
- Yeah!

45:56.416 --> 45:57.499
- We're alive.
- Ah!

45:57.500 --> 45:59.791
I did it. I saved us.

46:02.625 --> 46:04.083
You were saying?

46:32.291 --> 46:34.333
Okay. Okay.

46:34.500 --> 46:36.208
No... No more water.

46:36.375 --> 46:38.416
Tell me you can track them
down river.

46:38.583 --> 46:40.833
We can track them anywhere.

46:41.000 --> 46:43.583
They can run,
but they can't hide.

46:44.958 --> 46:47.291
So just to be clear,
we're not in this story?

46:47.458 --> 46:48.749
It feels a little bit like

46:48.750 --> 46:50.750
Kiros is stealing
my thunder here.

46:50.916 --> 46:52.916
Yeah. You know,
I don't feel seen.

46:53.166 --> 46:54.707
No. There's a lotta stories
with all of us.

46:54.708 --> 46:55.790
Tell one of those!

46:55.791 --> 46:57.625
Can I make
one small suggestion?

46:57.791 --> 47:00.375
Less childhood trauma,
more meerkat.

47:00.541 --> 47:03.250
Rafiki, I know
who Taka's gonna be.

47:03.416 --> 47:06.000
Oh. Me too. It's so obvious.

47:06.166 --> 47:07.833
But maybe, just so we're on
the same page, tell me?

47:08.000 --> 47:09.708
- Is it Simba? Is it me?
- Pumbaa.

47:09.875 --> 47:11.666
Oh, wait. Am I Obasi?

47:11.833 --> 47:12.832
That makes no sense.

47:12.833 --> 47:14.041
But seriously,
I have one question.

47:15.708 --> 47:17.125
Am I Taka?

47:17.541 --> 47:20.875
♪ I did
it again, I did it again ♪

47:21.250 --> 47:24.915
Not that I'm counting,
but I saved your hide. Again!

47:24.916 --> 47:27.499
As much as
it kills you to say it,

47:27.500 --> 47:29.125
let's hear a little,
"Thank you, Taka."

47:29.291 --> 47:31.415
You want me
to thank you

47:31.416 --> 47:33.083
for pushing me
off a waterfall?

47:33.250 --> 47:35.582
Yes, and you're welcome.

47:35.583 --> 47:36.832
Look, it's not my fault

47:36.833 --> 47:38.249
crocodiles are simply
attracted to you.

47:38.250 --> 47:40.499
Don't...
Don't say that.

47:43.708 --> 47:46.708
♪ I did
it again, I did it...

47:48.125 --> 47:49.416
Mufasa.

47:50.041 --> 47:51.833
Is it them?
Is it the Outsiders?

47:52.000 --> 47:53.875
No.
She's right there.

47:54.041 --> 47:55.166
"She"?

47:57.625 --> 47:59.291
There's no place to run.

47:59.458 --> 48:00.875
We have your scent.

48:01.166 --> 48:02.207
My scent?

48:02.208 --> 48:04.708
I've been stalking
you two all night.

48:05.166 --> 48:06.708
That's not possible.

48:06.875 --> 48:08.333
Then
why did I circle you

48:08.500 --> 48:09.750
three times in this wood

48:09.916 --> 48:12.125
while you two were
chasing each other's tails?

48:31.625 --> 48:33.250
Uh... That's embarrassing.

48:33.791 --> 48:37.166
Yeah, well, I, uh,
meant to do that, so...

48:37.333 --> 48:39.250
Still think I'm afraid?

48:41.833 --> 48:42.999
Why are you
following us?

48:43.000 --> 48:44.415
I was hoping to find my pride.

48:44.416 --> 48:45.499
What happened to them?

48:45.500 --> 48:46.583
The Outsiders
happened.

48:47.041 --> 48:48.124
A few of us got away,

48:48.125 --> 48:50.833
but you're the only
other lions I've seen.

48:52.083 --> 48:53.083
You two better keep moving.

48:53.250 --> 48:54.500
Wait! Please.

48:54.666 --> 48:56.916
Um... My name is Taka.

48:58.083 --> 48:59.791
Son of Obasi.

48:59.958 --> 49:01.625
I know what it's like
to lose everything.

49:01.791 --> 49:03.041
Come with us. We can help you.

49:03.208 --> 49:04.791
I don't need any help.

49:04.958 --> 49:07.083
But you don't have anyone.

49:07.250 --> 49:09.875
She does indeed have someone.
Thank you very much.

49:10.041 --> 49:12.250
That's Zazu. Don't eat him.

49:12.416 --> 49:13.875
You heard her. Do not eat me.

49:14.041 --> 49:16.833
As a recent addition
to the King's Royal Guard,

49:17.000 --> 49:19.791
I must kindly ask you both
to move on.

49:19.958 --> 49:21.708
Thank you for stopping by.

49:21.875 --> 49:23.916
Your king hired a bird
to protect you?

49:24.208 --> 49:25.791
How high can you fly?

49:26.000 --> 49:28.625
- Mmm.
- Look, I needed a scout.

49:28.791 --> 49:30.375
Zazu was the last option.

49:30.541 --> 49:32.083
Well, next to last.

49:32.250 --> 49:34.083
Between Albert the Iguana
and I,

49:34.250 --> 49:37.833
His Majesty decided
on the underling with wings.

49:38.000 --> 49:40.791
And thus, I became the
lead scout for the princess.

49:40.958 --> 49:42.499
It's my third day,
going swimmingly,

49:42.500 --> 49:43.750
if I may say so myself.

49:43.916 --> 49:45.208
Sarabi, you can
say so as well.

49:45.375 --> 49:46.958
How far do you think
you'll get with a bird?

49:47.125 --> 49:49.082
How far do you two geniuses
think you'll get

49:49.083 --> 49:51.000
stumbling around,
running into each other?

49:51.166 --> 49:53.083
All the way to <i>Milele.</i>

49:53.250 --> 49:55.041
<i>- Milele</i> is nothing but a myth.
- It's not a myth.

49:55.208 --> 49:57.290
Circle of Life
and fairy tale herds.

49:57.291 --> 49:58.374
- You're chasing something...
- Honestly.

49:58.375 --> 49:59.457
- ...that doesn't exist.
- As If.

49:59.458 --> 50:02.000
I don't know that <i>Milele</i>
exists, but right now,

50:02.166 --> 50:03.333
it's the only hope we have.

50:03.500 --> 50:06.333
We don't need hope.
We need food.

50:07.708 --> 50:09.957
Um...
Good job, brother.

50:09.958 --> 50:11.915
Oh, real nice.

50:11.916 --> 50:14.333
There's trouble in the trees.
My first real trouble,

50:14.500 --> 50:15.999
and I am going to pass.
Not going.

50:16.000 --> 50:17.500
I am staying right here,
thank you.

50:17.666 --> 50:20.875
Come on, Sarabi. Looks like
there's dinner headed our way.

50:21.416 --> 50:23.125
Sarabi, if I may.

50:23.583 --> 50:26.375
He makes a valid point,
Your Highness.

50:26.666 --> 50:28.499
But, on the other hand,
he's a starving lion,

50:28.500 --> 50:30.458
he wants to eat me,
so I am slightly torn.

50:33.750 --> 50:35.915
I think that went quite well,
all things considered.

50:46.000 --> 50:49.500
<i>And now, Kiara,
this is where I come in.</i>

50:58.500 --> 50:59.500
Rafiki.

51:00.041 --> 51:02.708
Order! We will have order
in the Congress of Baboons.

51:02.875 --> 51:04.874
Tonight, a cheetah
came into our trees

51:04.875 --> 51:06.333
for the third night in a row.

51:06.500 --> 51:07.833
Almost took one of our own.

51:08.000 --> 51:09.000
It was Rafiki's fault.

51:09.291 --> 51:11.250
He summoned the beast
with his dreams.

51:11.416 --> 51:12.665
Rafiki
and his visions

51:12.666 --> 51:14.791
must be banished
once and for all.

51:14.958 --> 51:16.125
Rafiki tried to warn you.

51:16.291 --> 51:17.957
His dreams
conjure our enemies.

51:17.958 --> 51:20.000
He talks to the spirits,
summons the devil.

51:20.166 --> 51:21.165
What are you talking about?

51:21.166 --> 51:22.291
He's
done it before.

51:22.458 --> 51:24.416
His brother was chased
from these very trees,

51:24.583 --> 51:25.708
never to be seen again.

51:25.875 --> 51:27.083
Rafiki was just a child.

51:27.250 --> 51:29.749
A child born with a leg that
does not work.

51:29.750 --> 51:30.833
Yet somehow, he survived?

51:31.000 --> 51:33.458
It was Rafiki who found water
in the dry season.

51:33.625 --> 51:35.958
Who healed you, Inaki,
when you were sick.

51:36.125 --> 51:39.208
He speaks to the insects,
converses with the moon.

51:39.375 --> 51:40.832
Zala, you know
what will happen

51:40.833 --> 51:42.333
if you send him
down from the trees.

51:42.500 --> 51:44.291
He is <i>amelaaniwa!</i>

51:44.458 --> 51:45.458
A curse to us all.

51:45.625 --> 51:46.624
That's not true.

51:46.625 --> 51:47.707
He doesn't
belong here.

51:47.708 --> 51:50.666
All in favor of banishment,
cover one eye.

51:51.250 --> 51:52.416
How can you
trust him?

51:52.583 --> 51:54.375
Don't trust him,
and I don't trust his magic!

51:54.541 --> 51:55.541
He doesn't
belong here.

51:55.666 --> 51:57.416
He's not a baboon.
And he never will be.

51:57.583 --> 51:59.000
He's not one of us.

51:59.166 --> 52:01.125
And so, it is time.

52:01.291 --> 52:02.583
No, wait.

52:03.208 --> 52:04.625
Where will you go?

52:04.791 --> 52:07.208
Where I should have gone
long ago.

52:07.375 --> 52:09.416
To find all that was lost.

52:10.083 --> 52:11.166
My family.

52:11.333 --> 52:13.458
You can't survive on your own.

52:13.625 --> 52:14.958
Nobody can.

52:15.125 --> 52:17.500
And yet, here we are.

52:19.458 --> 52:20.750
Oh, Rafiki.

52:20.916 --> 52:25.375
The eye never forgets
what the heart has seen.

52:45.708 --> 52:47.000
It's all right.

53:12.000 --> 53:14.000
Hmm. <i>Jamaa.</i>

53:15.333 --> 53:16.333
Hmm.

53:20.750 --> 53:24.083
You can try to run, but I'm
afraid you won't get very far.

53:24.250 --> 53:26.041
And why would I run from you?

53:26.791 --> 53:28.750
Because we're lions.

53:28.916 --> 53:31.625
As in... [roaring] lions!

53:31.791 --> 53:34.249
A flea
can trouble a lion

53:34.250 --> 53:36.125
more than a lion
can trouble a flea.

53:36.291 --> 53:38.958
I don't think you understand
what's about to happen.

53:39.125 --> 53:40.625
There's no place
for you to go.

53:40.791 --> 53:42.583
I am going forward.

53:42.750 --> 53:44.166
I seriously doubt that.

53:44.333 --> 53:48.125
It is easy to doubt everything
when you know nothing.

53:48.291 --> 53:50.375
Can we get on
with this, please?

53:50.541 --> 53:53.833
If you take my life,
you will never find <i>Milele.</i>

53:54.000 --> 53:55.750
Wait, did you say <i>Milele?</i>

53:55.916 --> 53:58.750
That is where I'm going.
Toward the light.

53:58.916 --> 54:02.541
I have been there many times
in my dreams.

54:02.708 --> 54:04.708
My brother waits for me there.

54:04.875 --> 54:06.208
I've seen the tree.

54:06.375 --> 54:08.375
Can picture it. The two of us,

54:08.541 --> 54:10.041
together again.

54:10.208 --> 54:12.541
And why would anyone trust
a baboon's dream?

54:12.708 --> 54:14.958
Sometimes, a dream
is all you have.

54:15.125 --> 54:17.500
The only truth
that lives in you.

54:17.666 --> 54:20.125
Like the memory
of a great king.

54:20.291 --> 54:21.708
How did you know?

54:21.875 --> 54:25.166
Okay. Help us get to <i>Milele,</i>
and we will let you live.

54:25.333 --> 54:26.916
- Do we have a deal?
- No.

54:27.083 --> 54:28.250
